content: Using this app for 5 years of ski records, able to go back & recall ski days from a few years ago. I have to remember to turn it on and off as I begin and stop skiing. Two negatives, vertical accuracy is a little off but may be due to my phone and no new update for my Fitbit Versa. Update, 2/07/21 A recent update appears to have improved and deleted parts of the previous versions. Pros: Ski Tracks now recognizes where you are. Con: doesn't give you choice to include new data in season totals.
app keeps pausing by itself after losing signal or 3 hours past.. I have checked every power saving setting.. still pauses. workaround is to pause and start in manually before 3 hours passes

This app just works like it's supposed to for resort skiing. It keeps data such as duration, speed, location, slope angle, I wish it would let me edit or deselect certain stats... I have left it on on the drive home and I then shows the data from the drive and I haven't found a way to delete that, but other than it works well. Keep in mind on the app you can't really drill into the data beyond what the interface shows you.
Great way to capture ski memories.
Good
Great app been using for years! Back up your tracks and save externally before you buy a new phone. Thanks for a great product!

Seems to miss vertical on my Android product. My friend uses it with his iPhone and by midday has recorded about 1600 more vertical than my phone, even though we did the same runs together. I don't understand why I'm losing about 10% of my vertical each day.
Would be good to have dark theme to save battery as long as possible
Works great
It should track G FORCE. Besides that, very happy.

Good app for those interested in keeping track of their slope stats. Also good if your worried about your stats being cleared or lost, as you can backup your tracks. The only thing that bothers me, runs and lifts are both red, kind of difficult to tell them apart when looking back at your day. Suggestion, lifts = dotted and blue, runs = solid red.
Was happy until this year. It keeps stopping

Love how simple this app is, and how it doesn't use much battery. One issue: I end up accidentally pausing the tracking constantly. Unlocking my phone, and where the pause button is located makes an accidental press constant. I wish there were some sort of feedback if the pause button is pressed, or could move the pause button, or have double tap pause confirm.
This is hands down the best ski tracking app. Sure the interface is dated, but it tracks consistently and doesn't have any unnecessary fluff.

I've been using it for many years and it has always been just fine. Not great, just fine. The interface is tired and desperately needs a refresh. There also needs to be an easier way to sync activities directly (or automatically) to Strava, Garmin, and other social sports sharing services.
Excellent backup of histories. I have gone through 3 cell phones and still have all my history intact. No battery usage issues either. Like the satellite map mode.
No longer accurate on android
It would work great but stops recording after 4 hours. I would like to record the whole day.
Love the app. Use it every day on the slopes. I would love to see a history total. As every season together to get a lifetime total.
This is a great app. I wish it would start on its own, I guess i'm forgetful!
I love it!
Would love if there was an option to "trim" the end of your recording, as I've more than once forgotten to turn it off after my day. Had it for years though, highly recommend.

This was such a great app. Now it runs in the background all the time? Who's brilliant idea was that? 25% battery usage while not being on the slope and not thinking about the app. I force stop it now but unless you fix this it will no longer be used on my device. Sigh.
I love this app! I've been using it for 6 years and I love how it tracks every run, vert, speed - everything!
Doesn't work; can't find gps but several other apps, including maps, can. Checked permissions and it had location rights, reset the app and then reset the phone and still didn't work
The appis runni g but o ly records a couple of runs?????
Tracks perfectly
Thanks for the new update.
Seems to have gone wrong when it comes to distance and speeds these days

I used this for 2-3 years tracking ski stats and when set on "snowshoeing" for hikes - it worked great. Maybe 4-5 months ago it started dropping the GPS connection (that's a guess) on a regular basis, yielding useless maps and data. I deleted and re-installed several times, no luck. I hope they fix whatever went wrong, based on other reviews this isn't just my issue.

I've used it ever since I got my first android phone. It's NOT battery-hungry and NOT only for skiing and saves .gpx and .k* files to feed into google earth. It tries to interpret car trips into ski runs, which is kind of cool, but the saved files don't care what you were doing, just when and where you were. A warning: Turn off the 'battery monitor' unless you really need it -- I had forgotten about that setting and it stopped tracking 2/3 of the way through a car trip although there was 30% of the battery left. Google maps IS a battery hog, and that's what ate up the battery -- Ski Tracks had used only 3%. I liked it enough to pay money for it (it may be free now) AND the authors respond to email!

As well as skiing I use this app when out on my bike. Love the ability to show track on Google maps. Only problem is that it's altitude is way out for my home address and average speed is not working. Pixel XL.
Good app , even works on Android watch. Wish there was a Fitbit version.

I have spent 2 days trying to download this app. I finally made it to the page where you pay for it and download it. It shows as INSTALLED on the app download page but I can't find it anywhere on my phone. Can someone help?
Great app. I've had it for a few years now, and I love it.
Good

I love this app. Skiing was wonderful, the app never failed, ran each day w/o problems. Skied 16 days, what a mass of information. Truly a fantastic addition to my Epic Mix data. I am using the app now to track my walking. It works just fine. Doug....

The more I use this app and get to know it, the better I like it. Had to allow the app to access to location all the time so it would continue to record data without babysitting it. Also have to transfer photos to Google Photos by finding them in their folders and sharing/uploading to Google Photos. Otherwise it would be a 5...

GPS issues on android. Tried to import a corrected track from CoreCoders now it will not even open. Uninstalled and re-installed and still will not open. Says "Ski Tracks keeps stopping". Anyone k ow how to fix this problem?
Did not work at all.
Was working now will not connect to GPS on my new s9. I now am missing 3 times from going and this not connecting. Will be downloading a different app.

Doesn't work - save yourself $0.99 and use a free app

Could never get it to work. Tried installing the recommended GPS assistance apps, but this app never seemed to be able to figure out where I had gone. I would be looking at the GPS location, and ski tracks would tell me it had no signal for the past two minutes. Completely useless. On a Samsung S9+
Horrible app that works intermittently. Super unreliable.
Used to be good. Now just had permanent GPS issue and records nothing, other apps locate me fine so only issue is this app

works pretty well. very cool to look back at my trail. I use it for snowmobiling and it's obviously so much cheaper than garmin stuff. You can export your tracks and view them in google earth. It exports in .gpx or .kml. This app is definitely worth the dollar considering the cost of dedicated gps units.

It was a Great app But now it doesnt work I m skiing and it doesnt log the runs Looses gps I bought that app years ago and it's a shame it's broken now Dont really want to buy another one so please fix Maybe for next skiing season it will be back up Cheers

The app has been improved, I now find it reliable, and I like its playback feature. Its battery friendly, and keeps tracking even when in gondolas, or buildings. My only gripe is the lack of contrast bewteen text and background, and tiny font size when saving a track, its too easy to not save it by mistake, this ought to be fixed so deleting it is hard and required a separate dialogue.
replyContent: Hi Simon, we are sorry to hear you do not like the application. Please could you contact us on skitracks-android@corecoders.com so we can work together to resolve the problems you're having. Thanks.

content: Works beautifull1

This just doesn't stay connected to the Satellites, at least not at Powder Mountain on a very clear day. Useless. GPS issue notifications all day long and it didn't seem like it was ever recording stats even remotely accurately. The most accurate recording I got was during the bus ride to hop on the snowcat. Any way to get the $0.99 back? Junk.

My favorite ski app. In addition to it being a great way to track Vertical and other fun stats from your ski day, I had a recent glitch with a new phone and the tech support I received was outstanding as well.
Tis app works just fine on my S10+ I dont have any issues with GPS so far. It would be nice if I can add pictures from gallery and not only those i have taken within app.
Not accurate
Pretty useless, rarely works
Was 5 star but now it's double counting runs
Awesome app used every time I go skiing not sure why it has such a low rating pay the $2 no ads good stuff

I've used this app for the last 5 or so years and have raved about it, you didnt have to remember where you went during the day as the app recorded all this, it was so good I paid for the app. However, this week it couldn't be more rubbish! Recording 9 hrs a day and saying I did 1 run at 1mph, I uninstalled it thinking there was a glitch and reinstalled it 3 times! Nope stopped working, very disappointed.

Since this years update on Android the stats no longer make sense. For example, I did 11 runs at a small mountain today which has approximately 1,010 vertical. App shows 17 runs for 14,629 vertical. I love this app but the stats are garbage.
Keeps pausing randomly

Used to be the best ski tracking app out there. I have used it on a pixel phone for several years and this season it no longer works. It gives a GPS error every time I go skiing. I did troubleshoot the issue by referencing the developer's instructions.
enable all permissions, turn OFF power saving. used to be ok, now it lacks a lot of useful info for a paid app.

No lite version so paid for this one. It paused randomly and didn't actually record any of my snowboarding for the week! No obvious reason as to why, had the battery use setting adjusted and checked everything else. Considering it's an app I had to pay for I'm very disappointed.

Feb 2020 Pausing issue is gone but now once battery is below 30% it stops tracking and asks you if you want to continue. I have already changed it so battery doesn't optimized... content: Awesome tracking app! Vertical, speed, history, maps, integrate pics. If you don't have it, get it!

Really good app on the whole (and no adverts). There are quite a few places where UX could be improved, however. One major thing is the photos option. It is a great concept but the execution makes the feature basically worthless. I can't add photos from my gallery or Google phtots or general files (this is really annoying) . I can't edit photos. I can't add photos after the recording has ended. It doesn't show me a preview of the image when I take a photo so I thought it hadn't taken one at all

When I updated it this season, the GPS paused randomly for no reason and it lost track of my data. I had to babysit it all day. Never had this problem before in many years of use. Sony Xperia. UPDATE: After restarting my phone, the GPS pausing problem appears to have been resolved. I need another ski day to test it.

Accuracy is not the best especially when you compare the same tracks on 3 different phones and all are different. Also need to be able to edit the ski track so you can trim out wrong/incorrect recorded data. Link to smart watch or phone health app should be standard these days

Does not work on Samsung S10+. I have used this app on 3 previous versions of the Samsung Galaxy phones without any issue, so was very disappointed when for a recent ski trip all I got were GPS error messages.
It looks like it can do alot, but it says i only skid like 2 merer with 5,3 km/h can someone help me?
Perfect. Does everything you need and much more.

V good

UPDATE: even on a new device the polling frequency is too slow. ski tracks shows an erratic z-pattern. speeds measured are therefore inaccurate. Great if you don't turn. The author claimed in 2016 that they would fix this. Still waiting in 2020, guys!
replyContent: Hi David, thanks for your feedback and suggestions. We are currently working on a new algorithm that will fix both of the issues you described and more. Please keep an eye out for the update containing it. Thanks

This app worked well in the last however does not work this year. Tracking, speed and overall use has been drastically effected and has made the app useless on my Pixel 3

Useless. Can't ever find GPS. Pointless app. Don't install
Excellent app

The best app I have found for tracking skiing with plenty of data and nice overview for going through previous days. Have no complaint and no issues.

Been using the app for a few years, but this season the total vertical isn't being totaled correctly from all downhill runs in the breakdown. Pretty useless if we have a key data point showing an incorrect total. Please fix!
Brilliant for recording what you do each day and looking at stats at the end of the trip. Speed can be a bit off but who cares.
The best ski tracking app for android! Sadly UI design is really outdated.

Great app. Does what is says it does all the time. Been a user 5 years across several android platforms. Records all essential data for the day. Pause feature for lunch. Nice area map can replay your day and runs.

The rest of my stats seems pretty accurate but my map for the day will show multiple runs on a a single lift, 4 or 5 runs when I go down a single time. This app is definitely five stars without this one issue, wish I could give 4.5 stars.

The app has a great interface but lacks the accuracy of my Garmin Fenix GPS watch. I thought it might be my phone that was the problem but my skiing companion had the same issue. Both speeds and vertical drop were off by a huge margin. If you love this app I have news for you, no you weren't skiing that fast. Nowhere near. Nice collection of stats but if the data is garbage ......
Amazing! 6/5!!

Over the years I have had this app it has performed well. Unfortunately this year it has saved more days than I have skied. I skied and saved 7 days so far, it has multiplied those same days to 14. The first day it saved 4 times to history, other days twice. I am not doing anything different from the past when one day saved equaled one day. This is very disappointing!
A good app, very easy to use. GPS functions including speed, altitude and location tracking is accurate. Battery drain is minimal.
Could not get the altimeter to work regularly. It did for a while but hasn't worked for 6 months or so. I removed the app.
Very good

This app has worked well for me. It's been nice to be able to keep track of my skiing for the last 4 years. I do ski pretty fast but I do question if my maximum speeds are as high as it tells me. Only improvement I would love to see is to have it pause and restart automatically when I go inside for a break. It stops when it loses satellite when I go inside but doesn't start again when I go back out. I often don't remember to restart until part way down the hill.
Battery drains quickly but a very useful app

Doesn't work on Samsung S7 edge. I loved the app on my old Sony and raved about it to all my friends. Since I installed it on my S7 Edge it has never worked. Real pity because it used to be great. Come on ST team, get a fix out there ASAP.

2014 review: The app works great, better than most, except for one thing: it insists on thinking that I'm using lifts. 2019 update: this was nicely fixed, and I've used the app happily since for a wide range of activities, include water travel. great app. works great. just make the regording indicator a little more clear. i get confused if it's recording or not

content: doesn't work on Samsung S8, said my max speed was 22mph... we went faster than that on ski lifts

Would like to curse profusely in this review but will not in the hope someone will actually see it and avoid losing their data. Fix your app.
Very good app

Superb app for skiing.
it's a cool way to see the stats of your ski day.

Good app, but I wish there were more specific settings for units. It's either all US or all metric. I would like to see my speed in km/h, but my vertical in feet instead of meters.
doesn't work with android gps
great app

ive been using this for years. its a great tracker. fairly accurate. . if you want something to keep a record to look at the end of the day i highly recommend it.

content: I like the app a lot and have been using throughout the season, however, after the latest update, my speed seem to have increased a lot. Hit 65mph when my previous high was low 50's - yet I don't feel like I skiing faster than usual....

best ski tracker i know of

installed this for my second week of snowboarding. It does everything i need, and does it very well. I like the export to Google Earth for a 3-D view. But each of the analyses showed a different number! The speed is invariably overstated by about 30-40%. I'm searching for better ski apps.
Very good app but after 10 minutes it crashes on my Huawei P20 lite. Very sad because it has a very good potential.

content: I gave this only one star due to GPS problems, but since then I fixed the problem and managed to actually test the program. Old Review: GPS can never find enough satellites. Says 16/21 satellites at most, even at the top of a mountain in the Alps... Considering that 3 satellites are enough to triangulate the position within 30 meters, 16 should be more than enough. Absolute garbage.
replyContent:
Hello Eren,

16/21 Satellites is a fix, the total reported satellites might include those on the horizon coming into or going out of view, it is unlikely all 21 satellites can be accessible even on top of mountain.

If you have any technical questions please contact support@corecoders.com

content: This app is great! Definitely the best lightweight ski tracking app.  This app would be perfect if you could set a "base area" to automatically pause when you entered it, and resume when you left it. Make it customizable in shape and size, maybe with multiple selections.  At my home mountain, all 180 vertical feet of it, the app doesn't recognize each run as a run so I have to count the number of peaks in the altitude graph. A run counter that will automatically adjust to the mountain size would be great and the algorithm shouldn't be too hard to design.  Lastly, I would like to have an option to have a persistent notification when it's paused, reminding me to resume tracking when I head back out. That way I'm more likely to remember to resume it after lunch, or save it when I head out.  With a couple added features, hopefully the app will stay lightweight and be better all around worth 5 stars!
replyContent:
Thank you Jake for your review and feedback - much appreciated.

We are looking at geo-fencing to auto-start. With regard to run analysis will be available soon and will correctly detect smaller runs. 

Finally a pause/restart notification is a good idea and we will look into it.

Best ski tracker I've used so far, well worth whatever I paid for it. It has all the features and more that I could ever want for analysing my ski day and always seems accurate.   The android wear compatibility works great, it's easy to use even when access to your watch is restricted by gloves and thermals and coats as you just need to swipe to navigate the stats pages, each of which provide all the info you want without getting your phone out.   Also it stays on the page you last left it on when the watch goes onto ambient/sleep so you can leave it on your favourite page for quicker access. Only thing is that it does use noticeably more battery life than normal if you leave it open acting as the watch face as it requires the watch to be constantly running the app. However it's not so bad that the my watch (lg watch r) can't last the ski day running ski tracks - it loses around 50% on a 7 hour ski day with ski tracks open compared to around 30/40% with the app just open on the phone and the watch on a normal face. Maybe a few ski tracks watch faces we could download from the store would better for battery life.  One thing that would be good to see is google fit integration but that's not essential and I don't know if it's even possible.

Good app that mostly just works flawlessly and does almost everything I need. It doesn't consume too much battery and can be left in your pocket or rucksack all day long to reliably track your skiing . It then provides the data, maps and export options I want to review my day.  But I've downgraded my review from 5 to 3 stars because there have been few updates in recent years and long standing issues remain unresolved.  For example, once in every few days the apps randomly stops tracking. This happens on all my family's phones (Sony and Samsung). Also, it can't handle downhill lift rides - it assumes you're skiing. Finally, the average speed includes all stops, etc, so is meaningless. A record of the average moving skiing speed should be added. Would be good to see more developments so this app doesn't go "stale" and overtaken by alternatives.

This app exceeded my expectations.  I had some trouble using the full capability and contacted the developers.  They replied promptly with the info I needed.  Now that I have full use of the app it is even more awesome that I had assumed initially.  Great fun for skiers, snowboarders & even hikers.  Have not used all battery capability even though the first use was 8+ hours.  I recently upgraded my phone and wanted to transfer 2 years of history to my new phone.  I contacted the developer and he sent me an e-mail that walked me through the process.  My entire history did not transfer so I contacted him again and he promptly asked me to send him the files I had attempted to transfer.  He found a glitch in some of them and e-mailed the revised files to me.  I was able to load them and my history is now complete.  The whole process took only a few days.    GREAT APP and GREAT SUPPORT!!!!

content: We left Ski Tracks on during the drive home.  My buddy's read a vastly different top velocity speed (iphone) versus mine (android).  Perceive there is a significant calibration issue.

This should be broken down into 3 numbers: overall average, ascent average, and descent average.  (3) There's no way to save the results for capture in Excel, or to backup and move to another phone. replyContent: Hi Mike, 1) this is due to your data being ran through more complex algorithms and filters upon saving to give more accurate statistics. We are working on improving this. 2) This is incorrect and will be changed in the future 3) There isn't a file type importable into Excel. You can move your tracks in SKIZ format. Email us for more info.

This app would have been fantastic. It has some excellent stats, and most of the time seems to just do the right thing, when left running in the background. It's a shame it's spoiled in a few ways:  First, it doesn't use Android intents properly; want to share to Google Drive - you have to click 'share', which *should* launch an intent picker, but doesn't. You then have to select "email", and then you get the intent picker. Rather than having sharing to Facebook etc. built in, the app should just use native Android intents - if I have the Facebook app installed, use that; otherwise, don't present it as an option. I presume this is an artefact of an iPhone port or something.  Second, and more critical, the app refused to start because it couldn't contact a license server. I was abroad, and had a choice of incurring roaming data fees, or not using it. Not a great choice.

After trying (and failing) to use AlpineReplay, I decided to give the Android port of Ski Tracks a try, recording my last two days in Lake Louise, and despite it being a rather young port, I'm quite impressed!  About my only major complaint (echoed by a friend who regularly uses the iPhone version) is that it appears to have lost track of my last run of the day, which is a shame since I broke my speed record during that run (though it did retain a record of the speed attained, there's simply no record of it under the run breakdown).  Aside from that it worked great!  Barely a hit to the battery life (my Nexus 4 had ~60% after 6 hours on the mountain) and excellent tracking.  The on-device analysis and visualization is very nice (integrating with Google Maps means you also get labeled runs on supported resorts), and export to KML + Google Drive made it dead easy to view runs directly in Google Maps and Earth.  About the only other obvious thing lacking is more sharing options... what fun is tracking your ski runs if you can't reach narcissism nirvana by sharing with all your uninterested friends?  Facebook and email support is there, but I'd love to see support for posting to G+.
I love this app. Just used it at Killington and worked great each day of the trip. Just wish it would run/be compatible on my v2.3 Moto Droid, an old phone I'd like to repurpose.

replyContent: Hi Albert. Please try updating to the latest version. This should fix your issue. We're sorry for the inconvenience. Please contact us further if this does not solve your issue.

content: Only ever recorded 2 or 3 runs  and then stopped. Works fine on my wife's IPhone is the gps naff on the galaxy3??
replyContent: Hi Tom. It may that your device is dropping its GPS fix. Please read some troubleshooting methods located in our Android User Guide on our website. If you need any further assistance please do not hesitate to contact us.

content: When using regular sportstracker for a day, it consumes 50% of battery. This app eats almost 100% in 5 hours!
Works well to track ski runs,verticle, speed, elevation, and history. Map and profiles work well. Would be five stars if able to post to Facebook without sharing my friends with Tracker!!
Have android version for Samsung s3 mini. Simply doesn't work properly.
The app won't install on my phone. I keep getting error message 403.I tried clearing the cache and rebooting the phone several times to no avail

I used this APP every day on a five day ski trip to Killington VT and Mad River Glen VT. It worked perfect with no issues. At lunch time I would pause the APP until returning to the slopes. Skied a total of 70 miles during the trip. APP is easy to use and customer support is great.
Works good just make sure u change the measurement units right away. Still had a battery problem
It is almost the perfect app. It misses a zoom in on the graphs and a max speed per lap feature.

This is a great ski app. It provides you with so many useful statistics and the interface is very well designed and simple to use. Plus,  considering everything you get with this app, the price is extremely reasonable. Def worth it even if you don't ski that much.
Excellent performance and accurate readings.
Can get phresheez for free. Does the same and then more.

Doesn't include any resort maps - everything is just traced against Google Maps API.  For a paid app, I would expect better information on resorts, trails, restaurants, etc.  I've found other free apps that have more info with the same tracking functionality.
Love it! Really useful to  analyse my day on the slopes

GPS was not working on gaxaly note 2 & emailed the developer & got back a quick a response with help 2 fix the problem. & ended up being a new released update to fix bug so thank you for your customer service.
Brilliant app. Had seen this on iphone and used similar ones on android but now this has full android functionality its far and away the best. Can't wait to get on slopes again .

I downloaded this app hoping to track my runs in steamboat, the app won't read my GPS,  other apps work and read the signal,  this app does not,  it does not work at all.  I want my Dollar back please
It keeps crashing right after start. Just FC and that is it.  Crashing on Galaxy Note - 4.1.2 Samsung official
As promised I give five stars for implementing that feature!

Ski Tracks is awesome on iOS and it's great to see Android getting the same functionality at last. I'm on a skiing holiday at present and friends with iPhones were showing me the individual run details and then sharing via Facebook. I sadly couldn't do either... Until v1.1! Excellent!  However, in v1.1, the screen that shows individual runs doesn't show the final run of the day. For example it shows the cable car up the mountain but not the run down!

Used at Nevis Range on a cloudy day. No issues.  But it's a bit meh. The interface seems quite limited ,  options and details are few. I took some pictures but can't upload to anywhere like Facebook or Google. This app would be great if it interacted with the  rest of the world.
used  it for a week in Italy and all the functions worked perfectly. It doesn't tell you what specific runs you've been on and your tidings for them like some other apps
Seems to be very light on the battery which is nice. Export pictures and detailed statistics would be nice. Looking forward to facebook integration.
Does exactly what it says, exceeded my expectations. Now that I have this, I simply won't ski without it!
Looked good the first time I ran it, but it's been crashing on start every time since. Not good enough for a free app, never mind a paid one.
replyContent: Hi Andrew. Since V1.0.2 we have made many improvements, add new features and fixed many bugs. Please update to the latest version. We hope you will enjoy using the application.

content: Good application but lacks a lot of iOS functions. Also there is a weird bug I would say, I cannot see any information on map (like it is blank). In recording and history.  Please fix it.
Great little app, fun to record your whole days boarding! Publish to Facebook would be a great enhancement!
Not as good as iOS version barely functions
It's a good app which could be great if it had the same functionality as the iPhone version, particularly the ability to look at individual runs.
I was stoked to use this but I can't. Get lake Louise. Sunshine and Castle please!
Saw this a while ago on a friend's sheep phone. Great to see it now on Android.
Every this is good and I like how you can track your runs.
This app is fantastic to look at after a hard slog on the moutain. But please update app like the iPhone so i can share info on facebook etc
Get a cannot validate license error on start up every time. Any advice? Going snowboarding tomorrow.

Used this app for the first time today and am generally happy but it's lame that you can't share to Facebook etc.  It would be nice to be able to name the track too.  I might try other trackers that offer sharing options.. Close, but no cigar.
replyContent: Hi Deke. We have included Facebook sharing in the application. Please update to the latest version of Ski Tracks to have this feature. Also to name a track, touch the activity icon in the top right of the track statistics view and you will be able to edit your track details. Please do not hesitate to contact us for more information.

content: Missing individual run tracking and other features.
Waste of money Crashes all the time Work for 1 run Then crash crash crash crash crash crash crashj
replyContent: Hi Tony. Since V1.0.2 we have fixed many bugs, made many improvements and added new features. Please update to the latest version of Ski Tracks. Please do not hesitate to contact us regarding any questions or issues.

content: Tested it out alongside the iPhone version, had no problem recording the track. Would be nice to have all the options as ios version, especially statistics on every run I made. Also, ios version is cheaper, ($0.99 instead of $1.27). Higher price, less options = less stars.
Using this alongside iPhone owning friends. Stats very comparable. Looking forward to the extra analysis features.
Great app with amazing Dev support! The few issues that there were on launch were fixed very quickly indeed. Keep up the great work!
Was the best app on the iPhone. So glad its now on Android... cant wait to get on slopes this weekend.
This was the one app i was so sad to see wasnt on the playstore after switching from apple, and now it is! Yes!
So glad finally  on android. Have used it on the past skiing trips on the sheep phone. .had to borrow it. Great app  no data used and great to compare stats at the end of the day.

This was one app I really missed when moving from the iPhone to Android.  No need to keep an out of date database of a limited number of ski resorts, this app gives you a map of wherever you happen to be and tracks your progress over the terrain.  You get all your stats and you can replay your day when you get home which is rather entertaining.  Doesn't eat your battery and works without a data connection.  Fantastic! Oh, and it also tracks cross country skiing too.
